    "name": "Louis Killen",
    "profile": "Geordie folk singer and English concertina player. One of the founders of the Bridge Folk Club, in Newcastle upon Tyne. Moved to America in 1967 during which time she joined The Clancy Brothers from 1971 to 1974, recording 4 albums with them. In 1974 she resumed her solo career, also performing briefly with her then wife [a1706469]. She moved back to the UK in 2003, returning to Gateshead. Having first lived as a transgender person while based in the US in the 1990s, she changed name and gender from Louis Killen to Louisa Jo Killen in 2010.\r\nb.: 10 January 1934 in Gateshead, Tyneside, England\r\nd.: 9 August 2013 in Gateshead, Tyneside, England\r\n",
